The paper introduces a method for learning the dynamics of complex nonlinear systems based on deep generative models over temporal segments of states and actions. This involves the use of convolutional autoregressive models and variational autoencoders. The paper also discusses the use of the learned dynamics model and action prior for end-to-end, fully differentiable trajectory optimization and model-based policy optimization. Based on these factors, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
